where "formula_10" is a <a href="metalogic">metalogic</a>al <a href="Symbol%20%28formal%29">symbol</a> representing "can be replaced in a <a href="Formal%20proof">proof</a> with."

"Associativity" is a property of some <a href="logical%20connective">logical connective</a>s of truth-functional <a href="propositional%20logic">propositional logic</a>. The following <a href="logical%20equivalence">logical equivalence</a>s demonstrate that associativity is a property of particular connectives. The following are truth-functional <a href="tautology%20%28logic%29">tautologies</a>.

